name: Grilled Tilapia
author: rjholtz
summary: Easy, flavorful tilapia grilled over flames!
ingredients: 1 teaspoon lemon-pepper seasoning, or to taste
1 teaspoon ground cumin, or to taste
1 teaspoon dried mustard, or to taste
directions: Mix olive oil, lemon pepper, cumin, paprika, dried mustard, and garlic powder together in a small bowl
Brush each tilapia fillet with mixture using a pastry brush
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate for 1 hour
Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate
Spray a large piece of foil with cooking spray and place on the grill
Cook fillets on the preheated grill until they're easily flaked with a fork, about 5 minutes per side
